{
  "texts": [
    "The conservation of the 16S rRNA gene and the length of the amplicon product restrict the achievable taxonomic resolution.",
    "This means that certain closely related taxa may be difficult to differentiate based solely on the 16S rRNA gene sequence.",
    "Approaches based on the long reads sequencing (e.g.",
    "Oxford Nanopore and Pacific Biosciences), able to cover the whole 16S rRNA and ITS regions, are promising in reach species level taxonomic resolution (Johnson et al., 2019; Notario et al., 2023).",
    "(II) Inherent limitations in functional profiling: this approach attempts to estimate functional capacity using the 16S rRNA gene, it inherently lacks the ability to directly analyze the functional potential of microbes or microbial genes."
  ]
}